        testing
          reached:step_2
          censused,records=6,all_cid
          see:each chunk carries the origin content-address — a per-seq cid minted beside the whole-file body hash
          honest,landed,no_breach,on_disk,dropped
          see:an honest record lands clean — every chunk hashes to its promised cid so the file materializes on disk and the mirror card drops
          poison,seq:2,breached,no_new_land,gone,retained,gate_named
          see:a single poisoned chunk breaches the landing — its bytes no longer hash to the origin cid so the gate refuses it and nothing new lands
          see:the per-chunk gate localized the breach — it named the exact corrupt seq (what a whole-file hash never could) deleted the half-written file and left the record in the mirror for a retry
